    <!-- 03 MODEL -->
    <div class="panel" id="panel-model">
      <div class="panel-eyebrow">Business model</div>
      <h2>Three model pivots in 12 months — and what each one signals about the team's thinking</h2>
      <p>Ownly's commercial model has changed three times before the official launch. Reading that sequence tells you more about the real constraints than any press release does.</p>

      <div class="journey">
        <div class="j-step">
          <div class="j-num warm">Jun '25</div>
          <div class="j-content">
            <h3>Announced: 8–15% restaurant commission</h3>
            <p>Original plan — undercut Zomato/Swiggy's 17–30% with a flat 8–15% rate. Reasonable wedge play: restaurants save money, Ownly earns something. <strong>Abandoned before the pilot launched.</strong> Likely because NRAI wouldn't endorse a commission model, however discounted.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="j-step">
          <div class="j-num warm">Aug '25</div>
          <div class="j-content">
            <h3>Pilot: restaurants paid the delivery cost</h3>
            <p>Zero commission on order value, but restaurants shouldered delivery — ₹59 for orders above ₹400, ₹29.50 for ₹100–₹400. Gave Ownly delivery revenue without a commission label. <strong>Abandoned at city-wide launch</strong> — likely because this still felt like a cost to restaurants, undercutting the "free" positioning that NRAI was marketing on their behalf.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="j-step">
          <div class="j-num">Mar '26</div>
          <div class="j-content">
            <h3>Current: customers pay everything (₹30 flat)</h3>
            <p><strong>Restaurants pay zero. Customers pay ₹30. That's it.</strong> No commissions, no platform fees, no ad revenue, no subscriptions. All revenue is delivery fee × order count. This is where Ownly operates today — and where the unit economics problem lives.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="compare-grid">
        <div class="compare-card terra">
