      <div class="callout green">
        <b>The mobility playbook already proved this works once</b>
        Rapido killed per-ride commissions for auto and cab drivers, replaced with subscriptions, and became India's largest ride-hailing platform — 73.96M monthly users vs Uber's 39.05M (Jan–Feb 2026). Subscription income surged 14× to ₹275Cr in FY25 alone. <strong>This is the playbook Ownly is explicitly trying to repeat in food.</strong> The question is whether food delivery allows the same structural move that ride-hailing did.
      </div>
